ProcedureHelp.#cdata:
Syntax: PROC MAPIMPORT OUT= map-data-set DATAFILE= 'path-to-shapefile' <CONTENTS> <CREATE_ID_>;  
      EXCLUDE 'field-identifier(s)';  
      ID 'field-identifier(s)';  
      RENAME 'field-identifier-1' = variable-name-1 < ... 'field-identifier-n' = variable-name-n>;  
      SELECT 'field-identifier(s)';  

The MAPIMPORT procedure enables you to import ESRI shapefiles (spatial data formats) and 
process the SHP files into SAS/GRAPH traditional map data sets. 

The MAPIMPORT procedure does not produce any graphics output. Instead, it produces an output 
map data set, which can be used with the GMAP procedure.
